{
  "id": "019cfbf5-44b0-7c00-a6e2-2049f7694f63",
  "content": "## Pipeline Improvements — 8-Step Refactor (2026-03-17)\n\nCommit `f53e2a9` on `main` implements 8 improvements across all 6 pipeline scripts (00-05). Key decisions:\n\n### 1. Shared Utilities — `scripts/pipeline_utils.py` (NEW)\nExtracted duplicated functions from all 6 scripts into a single module:\n- `find_workspace_root()`, `load_config()`, `configure_logging()`, `validate_date()`\n- `VIDEO_EXTENSIONS`, `IMAGE_EXTENSIONS`, `discover_clips()`, `discover_images()`\n- `deduplicate_clips()`, `resolve_working_paths()`, `check_legacy_working_dir()`, `get_progress_bar()`\n\n`__file__` resolution still works because `pipeline_utils.py` is co-located in `scripts/` — the 4-parent walk (`scripts/ → dorea/ → repos/ → workspace/`) is unchanged.\n\n### 2. Date Validation\n`validate_date(date_str)` uses regex `^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$` — format-only, no calendar validation. Called immediately after `parse_args()` in scripts 01-05. Script 00 has no `--date` flag (one-time LUT generation).\n\n### 3. Clip Deduplication\n`deduplicate_clips(clips, prefer=\"raw\")` deduplicates by stem when same clip exists in both `footage/raw/` and `footage/flat/`. Prefers raw (preserves D-Log M dynamic range). Uses `\"raw\" in path.parts` for detection. Applied in scripts 01, 04, 05. Script 03 already handles via `find_source_video()` (raw-first search order, debug log added).\n\n### 4. SAM2 Auto-Download\n`download_sam2_weights()` in script 03 downloads from Meta's servers using `urllib.request` (stdlib). Atomic `.pt.tmp` → `.rename()` prevents partial downloads. Progress logged every 10%. Falls back to manual URL on failure. Replaces the old exit-on-missing block.\n\n### 5. Date-Scoped Working Directories (BREAKING)\nAll working paths changed from `working/{type}/{clip}/` to `working/{type}/{date}/{clip}/`:\n- `working/keyframes/{date}/{clip}/`\n- `working/scene_analysis/{date}/{clip}.json`\n- `working/masks/{date}/{clip}/{label}/`\n- `working/depth/{date}/{clip}/`\n\n`resolve_working_paths(workspace_root, config, date)` is the single source of truth. `check_legacy_working_dir()` warns if non-date-scoped data exists (called in script 01, the pipeline entry point).\n\n**Breaking change**: Existing data under old paths won't be found. No auto-migration — warning only.\n\n### 6. tqdm Progress Bars\nAdded `tqdm` to `requirements.txt`. `get_progress_bar()` returns tqdm if stderr is TTY, plain iterable otherwise. Applied in scripts 01, 03, 04 with log fallback for headless/batch runs.\n\n### 7. Pass 2 Refinement (Script 02)\nAfter Pass 1, for each detected subject: get source FPS via ffprobe, approximate source frame from keyframe number, extract ~13 frames in a 120-frame window (step 10) into a temp dir, send to Claude for exact first-appearance frame, update subject data with `pass2_refined: true` flag, re-write JSON. New flags: `--skip-pass2` (off by default). Skipped in `--dry-run` mode.\n\n### 8. Resolve Dry-Run (Script 05)\n`--dry-run` validates all inputs (footage, scene analysis, masks, depth, LUT, DRX) and shows per-clip summary with issue count. Returns before any Resolve connection. Enables testing from devcontainer.",
